WEBVTT

00:00.015 --> 00:01.522
There's something I need to tell you.

00:01.525 --> 00:03.406
It's not Jon's baby.

00:03.785 --> 00:05.514
EDDIE: How do you come back from a lie...

00:05.534 --> 00:06.484
I'm looking for Barbara Morgan.

00:06.494 --> 00:08.842
I think she may know things
about my husband.

00:09.195 --> 00:10.265
...once it's out there?

00:10.275 --> 00:11.590
BARBARA: Jon was supposed
to be on that flight.

00:11.600 --> 00:13.721
He wouldn't let himself move past it.

00:13.731 --> 00:15.224
I had to. I was pregnant.

00:15.785 --> 00:16.641
It keeps growing...

00:16.980 --> 00:19.180
Your son doesn't know
what happened to his father.

00:19.470 --> 00:19.860
...until...

00:19.980 --> 00:21.300
Mitch is his father.

00:21.790 --> 00:22.689
...it consumes you.

00:22.700 --> 00:24.932
I'm not calling for help.
I'm calling to volunteer.

00:25.275 --> 00:26.600
So, you have to face it...

00:26.885 --> 00:28.621
REGINA: Everywhere I turn,
there's Andrew stepping on my toes.

00:28.790 --> 00:30.581
He's the reason we're
open in the first place.

00:31.100 --> 00:31.910
...hope for the best...

00:31.990 --> 00:33.335
Maggie, you're in remission.

00:33.355 --> 00:34.368
Oh, thank God.

00:34.371 --> 00:36.480
[LAUGHS]

00:36.995 --> 00:37.720
...and trust...

00:37.870 --> 00:39.510
Don't be so hard on your mom.

00:39.600 --> 00:41.000
We all cope in different ways.

00:41.490 --> 00:42.804
...that it's not too late.

00:42.814 --> 00:45.820
♪

00:48.487 --> 00:52.556
[BALTHAZAR'S "WRONG VIBRATION" PLAYS]

00:52.558 --> 00:54.524
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh, oh ♪

00:54.526 --> 00:56.793
♪ Oh-oh, oh, oh-oh-oh ♪

00:56.795 --> 00:59.162
Hey, Gare, um, for the next two days,

00:59.164 --> 01:01.064
can you say you don't like Indian food

01:01.066 --> 01:03.800
so that when my mom is here
and we don't get Indian food,

01:03.802 --> 01:04.980
I can say it's your fault?

01:05.620 --> 01:06.820
Stranger things have been asked.

01:06.830 --> 01:08.150
[SIGHS]

01:09.680 --> 01:10.415
Why are you so nervous?

01:11.100 --> 01:12.215
She's only coming in for the weekend.

01:12.225 --> 01:14.711
Yeah, about that. Um, when
she gets here, can you...

01:14.713 --> 01:15.870
Ah, ah. Don't say it.

01:16.390 --> 01:18.203
Your mother and I got
in one little argument

01:18.210 --> 01:20.844
over a parking spot that she stole.

01:21.390 --> 01:22.873
- Now we get along great.
- [CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

01:22.999 --> 01:24.695
She even texts me sometimes.

01:24.700 --> 01:25.168
What?

01:25.670 --> 01:26.540
Nothing inappropriate.

01:26.550 --> 01:28.169
- [CELLPHONE BUZZES]
- Usually.

01:28.171 --> 01:28.617
[CHUCKLES]

01:29.580 --> 01:30.340
Ugh. Her cab's here.

01:30.870 --> 01:32.820
Listen, I know you
get along with my mom.

01:33.200 --> 01:35.100
The thing is... and I may
have mentioned this before...

01:35.470 --> 01:36.190
I don't.

01:38.680 --> 01:40.480
Maggie, what's the big deal?

01:40.482 --> 01:42.182
When she came in for your surgery,

01:42.184 --> 01:43.717
it was a very successful visit.

01:43.719 --> 01:45.518
Oh, because she was
only here for one day

01:45.520 --> 01:47.020
and I was heavily sedated.

01:47.022 --> 01:48.094
Hi!

01:48.133 --> 01:50.323
Hi!

01:50.325 --> 01:52.016
Well, don't just stand there.

01:52.019 --> 01:53.325
Give me a hug!

01:53.328 --> 01:54.928
- There's my guy!
- Oh. Oh. [CHUCKLES]

01:56.198 --> 01:57.797
Saving the best for last.

01:57.799 --> 01:58.798
Oh. Mm.

01:58.800 --> 01:59.599
Hi.

01:59.601 --> 02:00.567
Ah, get your bag.

02:00.569 --> 02:01.835
Oh, no, no, no, Gare, I got this one.

02:01.837 --> 02:04.304
Why don't you, uh, get
what's in the trunk.

02:04.306 --> 02:07.841
Oh, that pink wig is just so cute!

02:07.843 --> 02:10.143
I really need to get one
of these. [CHUCKLES]

02:10.145 --> 02:12.679
This last haircut is just
not what I wanted it to be.

02:12.681 --> 02:14.214
It... It's...

02:14.216 --> 02:15.215
GARY: Wow.

02:15.217 --> 02:16.336
Patricia, this is, uh...

02:16.339 --> 02:18.337
a lot of bags for just the weekend.

02:18.790 --> 02:20.306
Yeah, Mom, it's... [CHUCKLES]

02:20.316 --> 02:22.070
it's just the weekend, right?

02:23.280 --> 02:25.080
Yeah, well, um...

02:25.765 --> 02:28.731
I was hoping to find the
right time to say this,

02:28.741 --> 02:29.450
but, um...

02:31.310 --> 02:32.240
I've left your father.

02:32.250 --> 02:35.405
♪

02:35.990 --> 02:36.988
It's this way, right?

02:36.998 --> 02:41.908
♪

02:42.880 --> 02:46.332
I swear, she did not
text me any of this.

02:46.342 --> 02:48.481
♪

02:49.380 --> 02:50.980
- Synced and corrected by <font color="#D81D1D">VitoSilans</font> -
-- www.<font color="#138CE9">Addic7ed</font>.com --

02:54.528 --> 02:56.345
[GRUNTS]

02:56.348 --> 02:58.764
But, Mom, this does not make any sense.

02:58.766 --> 03:01.000
You guys have been married for...

03:01.002 --> 03:02.157
32 years.

03:02.160 --> 03:04.802
You see, this is exactly why
I didn't want to bring it up.

03:04.805 --> 03:05.871
I really...

03:05.873 --> 03:07.548
I really didn't want to upset you.

03:07.551 --> 03:08.617
Well, I'm upset.

03:08.620 --> 03:10.386
- I'm very upset.
- [SIGHS]

03:10.389 --> 03:12.517
Why are you not more upset?

03:12.520 --> 03:15.780
The fact is, your father
and I want different things.

03:15.783 --> 03:16.985
So, you're leaving him

03:16.988 --> 03:19.851
because he doesn't want to
take a Zumba class with you?

03:19.854 --> 03:21.899
GARY: [CHUCKLES] Zumba.

03:21.902 --> 03:23.968
I'm sorry, babe. Please... continue.

03:23.971 --> 03:27.059
Your father is a wonderful man.

03:27.061 --> 03:28.494
Who, last I checked, loves you.

03:28.496 --> 03:31.263
But there are different
ways to show love, sweetie.

03:31.265 --> 03:34.533
And some of the ways he's
been showing it lately just...

03:34.535 --> 03:35.901
[INHALES DEEPLY]

03:35.903 --> 03:37.703
...aren't what I need right now.

03:37.705 --> 03:40.906
Okay. But after 32 years,

03:40.908 --> 03:43.175
don't you want to try
to work through it?

03:43.177 --> 03:45.477
Maggie, when you went into remission,

03:45.479 --> 03:48.414
you realized you had your
whole life ahead of you,

03:48.416 --> 03:51.851
and I realized that...

03:51.853 --> 03:53.185
I do, too.

03:54.689 --> 03:57.623
And the rest of my life...

03:57.625 --> 03:59.458
might not include your father.

03:59.460 --> 04:04.029
♪

04:04.031 --> 04:05.564
Here's a little fun fact, Dad...

04:05.566 --> 04:08.367
it's estimated that 1/3 of
the food we consume each day

04:08.369 --> 04:11.303
relies on pollination,
provided mainly by...

04:11.305 --> 04:13.606
you guessed it... bees.

04:15.209 --> 04:18.978
♪

04:18.980 --> 04:21.714
Oh. Just in case Mom comes back early.

04:22.984 --> 04:24.350
Great idea.

04:24.352 --> 04:26.218
But...

04:26.220 --> 04:29.521
those court cases can
really, really drag on.

04:32.560 --> 04:33.726
Hey, you know what?

04:33.728 --> 04:35.527
Later today, at Garden Day,

04:35.529 --> 04:38.130
I think you should share
all of those bee facts

04:38.132 --> 04:39.164
with your teachers.

04:39.166 --> 04:41.233
I tried, Dad. They don't listen.

04:41.240 --> 04:42.399
[CHUCKLES]

04:42.403 --> 04:44.069
♪

04:44.071 --> 04:45.304
Really?

04:45.306 --> 04:47.037
You know what? PJ's here, actually.

04:47.040 --> 04:48.351
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- I'm gonna ask him.

04:48.353 --> 04:49.635
- I'll talk to you, buddy.
- [TELEPHONE BEEPS]

04:49.637 --> 04:50.902
Hey.

04:50.905 --> 04:53.105
Hey, what were you doing out
in Brookline the other day?

04:53.915 --> 04:55.848
My friend with the Brookline PD said

04:55.850 --> 04:57.583
he saw you walking
around the neighborhood.

04:57.585 --> 05:00.419
What were you doing over there?

05:00.421 --> 05:09.628
♪

05:09.630 --> 05:11.597
Alright, if you really want to know,

05:11.599 --> 05:13.365
I was walking to my girlfriend's house.

05:13.367 --> 05:15.401
I didn't even know you had a girlfriend.

05:15.403 --> 05:17.814
W... Uh... what's her name?

05:17.817 --> 05:21.706
Why? You can call and...
see if my alibi checks out?

05:21.709 --> 05:22.775
No. I just...

05:22.777 --> 05:24.510
I'm telling the truth.

05:24.512 --> 05:27.379
'Cause we don't... we don't
lie to each other, right, Dad?

05:27.381 --> 05:31.116
♪

05:31.118 --> 05:32.818
Hey, make sure you're home for dinner.

05:32.820 --> 05:34.353
Sounds fun.

05:34.355 --> 05:36.789
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

05:36.791 --> 05:38.490
♪

05:38.492 --> 05:40.025
[SIGHS]

05:40.027 --> 05:46.265
♪

05:46.267 --> 05:48.133
Damn it.

05:48.135 --> 05:49.935
Barbara!

05:49.937 --> 05:52.471
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS IN DISTANCE]

05:52.473 --> 05:54.273
Mm. Needs more lemon, Albert.

05:54.275 --> 05:55.709
- More lemon, Chef.
- [CHUCKLES]

05:55.712 --> 05:57.485
- [CELLPHONE BUZZING]
- Ah.

05:57.488 --> 05:58.744
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

05:58.746 --> 06:01.013
Hey, D, I'm a little, uh, busy.

06:01.015 --> 06:02.793
Can we chat when you get here?

06:02.796 --> 06:04.396
Hey, quick... what's
the name of the song

06:04.399 --> 06:07.286
that goes ♪ Why are all
the people out there? ♪

06:08.820 --> 06:09.577
That's a song?

06:09.580 --> 06:11.713
Jon and I used to sing it
when the kids got cranky.

06:11.715 --> 06:15.150
I feel like it's a female
singer from the '80s.

06:15.152 --> 06:16.885
Or maybe it's a man,

06:16.887 --> 06:19.555
but, like, a really pretty man.

06:19.557 --> 06:21.323
Well, that could be
anyone from back then.

06:21.325 --> 06:23.459
- How's brunch going?
- Mm, super-busy.

06:23.461 --> 06:25.353
There's, like, a
45-minute wait right now.

06:25.356 --> 06:26.895
Really? That's great!

06:26.897 --> 06:28.797
- You sound surprised.
- No, no, no.

06:28.799 --> 06:30.399
It's just that...

06:30.401 --> 06:32.666
Andrew mentioned reservations were down.

06:32.669 --> 06:34.970
Uh, when did you speak to Andrew?

06:34.972 --> 06:37.075
And why isn't he talking
to both of us about this?

06:37.078 --> 06:38.841
He just stopped by this morning...

06:38.843 --> 06:39.908
with a baby gift.

06:39.910 --> 06:41.276
I'm sure he was planning to.

06:41.278 --> 06:43.045
- [DOORBELL RINGS]
- [SIGHING] Okay.

06:43.047 --> 06:44.719
Oy. Someone's at the door.

06:44.722 --> 06:46.088
Maybe they'll remember the song.

06:46.091 --> 06:48.050
It's like ♪ This is the
best thing I've ever done ♪

06:48.052 --> 06:50.352
♪ This is how you have fun ♪

06:50.354 --> 06:52.622
Anyway, I'll see you at brunch later.

06:52.625 --> 06:54.490
- [CRYING CONTINUES]
- Shh. It's okay.

06:55.926 --> 06:57.197
Barbara.

06:57.200 --> 06:59.700
BARBARA: I hope this isn't a bad time.

06:59.703 --> 07:01.271
♪

07:07.435 --> 07:09.049
[SIGHS] Sorry about that.

07:09.051 --> 07:11.952
It's... just been hard to get her down.

07:11.954 --> 07:13.754
She's so cute.

07:13.756 --> 07:15.689
She has Jon's eyes, huh?

07:15.691 --> 07:16.657
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

07:16.659 --> 07:17.791
MITCH: We won't keep you.

07:17.793 --> 07:19.960
Um, we've been getting these notices.

07:19.962 --> 07:21.862
Yeah, from, uh...

07:21.864 --> 07:23.564
from a Rutledge Trust.

07:23.566 --> 07:24.832
♪

07:24.834 --> 07:26.934
DELILAH: Oh, yeah. Right.

07:26.936 --> 07:30.004
We didn't get a chance to
talk about it when we met.

07:30.006 --> 07:32.339
Jon, uh...

07:32.341 --> 07:33.610
Jon left you money.

07:33.870 --> 07:35.028
Well, we don't want it.

07:35.497 --> 07:36.163
Mitch.

07:36.180 --> 07:38.239
You don't hear from
the guy for 17 years,

07:38.242 --> 07:40.543
then out of the blue, he leaves
you half a million dollars?

07:41.980 --> 07:42.846
Why would he do that?

07:44.100 --> 07:46.423
I... I just think that after 9/11

07:46.430 --> 07:48.968
and everything that happened,

07:49.098 --> 07:51.137
he just wanted to make up for it...

07:51.147 --> 07:53.108
for not being there
for you and your baby.

07:54.473 --> 07:55.266
You told her?

07:55.885 --> 07:57.525
No. No, no, no. I, uh, figured it out.

07:57.785 --> 07:59.899
It wasn't hard, w-w-with
you acting so crazy

07:59.902 --> 08:01.445
- the last time she came over.
- Why is it crazy

08:01.450 --> 08:03.024
that I don't want my son finding out

08:03.030 --> 08:04.776
that I've been lying
to him his whole life?

08:04.780 --> 08:07.360
♪

08:08.690 --> 08:11.591
MAN: It's just that
every day feels heavier.

08:11.593 --> 08:15.161
So, after a while, I start wondering

08:15.163 --> 08:17.364
if it's even worth
getting up in the morning.

08:18.934 --> 08:22.302
That must be really tough.

08:22.304 --> 08:26.006
Do you have anything to look forward to,

08:26.008 --> 08:28.208
even... even the smallest thing?

08:28.210 --> 08:29.476
Yeah.

08:29.478 --> 08:31.211
You taking your first call.

08:31.213 --> 08:33.046
- You're ready, Rome.
- Are you sure?

08:33.048 --> 08:34.981
I felt... I felt like I
greeted you too eagerly.

08:34.982 --> 08:36.349
Let's just do the hellos again.

08:36.351 --> 08:38.717
A-At a certain point, you're
just gonna have to dive in.

08:39.988 --> 08:41.453
What's going on?

08:44.159 --> 08:45.492
Nothing. You're right.

08:45.494 --> 08:47.327
I'm, uh... [SCOFFS]

08:47.329 --> 08:48.495
I'm ready.

08:48.497 --> 08:50.697
♪

08:51.860 --> 08:54.594
MAGGIE: Yeah, okay. Alright, Dad.

08:54.596 --> 08:56.396
I love you.

08:56.398 --> 08:57.730
Bye.

08:58.802 --> 08:59.983
Okay.

09:00.001 --> 09:02.101
What did he say?

09:02.103 --> 09:04.337
He was just as vague as my mom was.

09:04.339 --> 09:06.773
I don't understand.

09:06.775 --> 09:09.676
They made it through
the loss of their son.

09:09.678 --> 09:12.212
You would think that they
could get through anything.

09:12.214 --> 09:14.647
Well, a lot of parents
get divorced, okay?

09:14.649 --> 09:16.149
Mine are divorced.

09:16.151 --> 09:17.350
You will get through this.

09:17.352 --> 09:19.285
They're not getting divorced!

09:19.287 --> 09:22.264
They're just... using permanent words

09:22.267 --> 09:23.857
to describe temporary feelings.

09:23.859 --> 09:26.125
You're right. I'm sure
they'll figure things out.

09:26.127 --> 09:27.660
How can you say that?

09:27.662 --> 09:30.695
My mom brought her teeth-whitening kit.

09:30.880 --> 09:34.898
She's looking at apartments
right now in Boston.

09:35.300 --> 09:36.410
Why would she move here?

09:36.665 --> 09:38.180
It's not like we're even close.

09:38.373 --> 09:40.659
I'm feeling like we
should cancel brunch.

09:40.662 --> 09:41.048
No.

09:42.590 --> 09:43.106
No.

09:43.625 --> 09:44.918
The only thing getting me through today

09:44.921 --> 09:46.513
are Regina's bottomless mimosas.

09:46.990 --> 09:47.480
Okay.

09:48.610 --> 09:50.001
Go, idiot!

09:50.010 --> 09:51.948
[HORN BLARES]

09:52.290 --> 09:54.677
Yep. Alcohol is
definitely gonna help this.

09:58.372 --> 10:01.273
You keep chopping, Albert. I'll
grab another bottle of brandy.

10:01.275 --> 10:02.241
[SIGHS]

10:02.243 --> 10:03.342
[SNIFFLES]

10:03.344 --> 10:06.245
Hey, D, what's... what's wrong?

10:06.247 --> 10:07.279
Nothing.

10:07.281 --> 10:08.970
All of it. I don't know.

10:09.080 --> 10:11.402
I just feel so anxious...
about everything,

10:11.830 --> 10:13.238
and it's like Charlie's
picking up on it.

10:14.390 --> 10:15.105
She's a newborn.

10:15.115 --> 10:16.860
Maybe you're giving her
a little too much credit?

10:17.530 --> 10:17.900
[SIGHS]

10:18.159 --> 10:20.800
Well, babies can feel your... stress,

10:20.810 --> 10:23.081
just like that lactation
specialist said.

10:24.650 --> 10:25.510
Remember when she asked

10:25.520 --> 10:27.718
if there was anything
different about this pregnancy?

10:29.210 --> 10:30.570
It's not Eddie. It's me.

10:30.700 --> 10:34.790
There's just so many people
I feel like I'm failing...

10:34.800 --> 10:35.760
especially Jon.

10:35.869 --> 10:37.220
Sweetie, don't do this to yourself.

10:37.370 --> 10:38.428
I should have been there for him.

10:38.832 --> 10:41.432
I should have... realized
how much pain he was in,

10:41.500 --> 10:43.248
and now the one thing that he wanted...

10:44.084 --> 10:46.114
to leave Barbara that
money... I can't even do that.

10:46.614 --> 10:47.145
Why not?

10:47.688 --> 10:50.191
The... They just don't want it.

10:50.717 --> 10:51.567
And... [SIGHS]

10:52.410 --> 10:55.446
I just... I feel like I'm
failing him all over again.

10:55.897 --> 10:57.030
- Listen to me...
- Hey. Sorry for interrupting.

10:57.695 --> 10:59.691
Regina, there's about 70
people waiting for omelettes.

11:00.694 --> 11:02.150
Including one of them who says
he's an old friend of yours,

11:02.210 --> 11:02.963
wants to say hi.

11:03.570 --> 11:03.996
Oh. You should go.

11:04.000 --> 11:04.569
Okay.

11:05.271 --> 11:07.300
70 people. Not bad for a brunch service.

11:07.570 --> 11:09.220
Yeah, yeah. If only brunch
were seven days a week.

11:15.000 --> 11:15.861
- [CRYING]
- GARY: Oh, I know.

11:15.980 --> 11:18.344
It's tough having zero responsibility.

11:18.410 --> 11:19.016
I know.

11:19.761 --> 11:21.264
Sorry. I'll take her.

11:22.006 --> 11:23.807
That is my favorite
part of being an uncle.

11:24.036 --> 11:25.475
The tag out. You're it.

11:25.604 --> 11:28.294
Uh, D, this is Elon.
He's Regina's friend.

11:28.304 --> 11:29.813
He used to eat at her old
restaurant all the time.

11:30.183 --> 11:31.231
Oh, wow.

11:31.581 --> 11:34.494
You've known her longer than we have.

11:34.320 --> 11:35.280
I'm, uh, Delilah.

11:35.720 --> 11:36.403
Nice to meet you.

11:37.913 --> 11:38.907
I'm so sorry for your loss.

11:40.415 --> 11:40.990
Thank you.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.390
[LAUGHING] Oh, my goodness. Elon, hi!

11:43.400 --> 11:45.200
There she is. Come here, come here.

11:45.210 --> 11:46.758
- Oh, my goodness.
- Ohh!

11:47.342 --> 11:49.005
Gina, congrats on this new place.

11:49.010 --> 11:50.272
It looks fantastic.

11:50.280 --> 11:52.211
Well, you always told me
I'd open another restaurant.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.410
I may have predicted it,
but you made it happen.

11:54.420 --> 11:55.089
[LAUGHS]

11:55.718 --> 11:59.470
Oh, you guys, Elon is
a very talented psychic.

11:59.819 --> 12:00.901
Ha! [CHUCKLES]

12:01.536 --> 12:04.057
Oh. Yes, that's, uh,
definitely a real job.

12:04.645 --> 12:04.861
Thank you.

12:05.450 --> 12:06.538
How long has it been now?

12:06.680 --> 12:07.894
At least five years.

12:07.900 --> 12:08.520
[LAUGHS]

12:09.140 --> 12:11.105
Wait... You guys haven't
seen each other in five years?

12:11.313 --> 12:11.898
[BOTH CHUCKLE LIGHTLY]

12:12.575 --> 12:14.650
I... How did you know that, um...

12:14.810 --> 12:16.653
Oh. Sometimes I pick up on things.

12:17.880 --> 12:18.927
Sorry if I overstepped.

12:19.040 --> 12:21.077
Again, I'm so sorry for your loss.

12:21.200 --> 12:22.783
Come. See my beautiful kitchen, Elon.

12:22.990 --> 12:24.576
- Let me guess... it's this way?
- Ohhh!

12:27.520 --> 12:28.780
- That was weird.
- [CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

12:28.970 --> 12:29.539
Yeah.

12:29.690 --> 12:31.701
Gina hasn't spoken to him in five years,

12:31.803 --> 12:33.211
and he knew about Jon.

12:33.995 --> 12:34.921
I just got chills.

12:36.009 --> 12:36.880
You're under the vent.

12:37.790 --> 12:38.548
GARY: I'm sorry.

12:38.688 --> 12:40.842
I just don't buy into
any of that psychic crap.

12:41.772 --> 12:43.500
Elon told me that I was gonna

12:43.510 --> 12:45.431
open up another restaurant someday,

12:45.996 --> 12:46.799
and look where we are.

12:46.810 --> 12:48.850
Wait, you mean a very talented chef

12:48.860 --> 12:50.687
who's always dreamed
of opening a restaurant

12:50.900 --> 12:52.312
[GASPS] opened one?

12:52.713 --> 12:53.805
You'll understand if I don't run out

12:53.815 --> 12:54.897
and buy a lottery ticket.

12:55.207 --> 12:56.650
How do you explain
him knowing about Jon?

12:56.841 --> 12:57.203
Mm.

12:58.012 --> 13:00.436
I can't explain that, because
he didn't actually say "Jon".

13:00.510 --> 13:03.032
All he said was "Sorry for your loss",

13:03.180 --> 13:06.910
which is warlock speak for
"Your money will soon be mine."

13:07.603 --> 13:08.300
Okay, yeah.

13:08.310 --> 13:10.730
I-I think some psychics are scammers

13:10.740 --> 13:12.792
and some really have an ability.

13:12.932 --> 13:15.178
- Totally.
- What? You, too, Dr. Bloom?

13:15.392 --> 13:17.097
You have extra education.

13:17.237 --> 13:18.005
[CHUCKLES]

13:18.135 --> 13:19.393
Okay, you think he's the real deal?

13:19.530 --> 13:21.446
You should go ask him for the name
of that song you can't remember.

13:22.259 --> 13:24.177
Maybe I should see if
he'll give me a reading.

13:24.358 --> 13:25.368
I really think you should.

13:25.596 --> 13:26.231
No, I was kidding.

13:26.391 --> 13:27.974
D, with everything that
you were saying about Jon,

13:28.912 --> 13:29.517
it might help.

13:29.885 --> 13:31.769
Or you can give me 200 bucks,

13:32.197 --> 13:34.647
I can set it on fire and save
you the trip to Cambridge.

13:34.661 --> 13:35.063
[GASPS]

13:36.716 --> 13:39.121
But how did I know
he lives in Cambridge?

13:39.520 --> 13:40.403
[INHALES DEEPLY]

13:40.527 --> 13:41.788
Oooh!

13:43.000 --> 13:44.448
Make sure you really get my ears.

13:44.750 --> 13:45.323
Don't be shy.

13:45.658 --> 13:46.408
Did you pack all your stuff?

13:46.963 --> 13:48.160
- Gardening gloves?
- Check.

13:48.500 --> 13:48.795
Shovel?

13:49.100 --> 13:50.413
It's called a trowel, but check.

13:50.985 --> 13:51.831
Ears look good.

13:52.375 --> 13:53.479
Alright, turn around.
Let's do your face.

13:53.771 --> 13:54.907
Extra sunblock.

13:54.917 --> 13:55.856
Mommy!

13:55.868 --> 13:58.080
♪

13:58.109 --> 13:58.806
- Hey...
- Mommy!

14:00.008 --> 14:01.798
I missed you so much.

14:01.808 --> 14:08.590
♪

14:11.721 --> 14:13.274
How was your trial?

14:13.277 --> 14:16.616
Oh, I told him about... your big case.

14:16.619 --> 14:18.279
In the Grand Canyon.

14:19.482 --> 14:20.548
Yeah.

14:20.550 --> 14:23.484
I... That was a tough trial.

14:23.486 --> 14:25.986
They... wanted to fill
the whole thing up,

14:25.988 --> 14:27.396
and I told them, "No way."

14:27.399 --> 14:28.965
[CHUCKLES] Nice going, Mom.

14:28.968 --> 14:30.824
- Thanks, T.
- Oh, I forgot my canteen.

14:30.826 --> 14:32.526
I'll get it, and then we can go.

14:32.528 --> 14:33.761
[FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING]

14:33.763 --> 14:37.531
Hey, now that you're
back, you can come with us.

14:38.953 --> 14:41.129
Um, we were supposed
to go to Garden Day.

14:42.235 --> 14:44.091
I'll... I'll e-mail and
tell them we can't make it.

14:44.341 --> 14:45.822
No. We should go.

14:46.731 --> 14:47.636
He's looking forward to it.

14:49.124 --> 14:49.649
Are you sure?

14:49.789 --> 14:50.431
[SIGHS]

14:52.165 --> 14:53.433
The only thing I'm sure about right now

14:53.443 --> 14:54.811
is that I need to be there for him.

14:54.976 --> 15:00.107
♪

15:00.207 --> 15:00.480
CHRISTOPHER: Love note?

15:00.957 --> 15:01.547
Yeah.

15:02.267 --> 15:02.882
It's the wife.

15:04.123 --> 15:04.778
She's the best.

15:05.698 --> 15:06.764
Put her through a lot last year,

15:06.774 --> 15:08.032
and she was really there for me, man.

15:08.880 --> 15:09.241
Oh, yeah?

15:10.570 --> 15:10.780
Yeah.

15:13.885 --> 15:15.623
I know what it's like to
be going through all this.

15:16.992 --> 15:21.346
Not too long ago, I was
in a really... bad place,

15:21.506 --> 15:24.005
and a friend's call saved me.

15:26.384 --> 15:28.220
Now I might be the call
that saves someone else,

15:28.230 --> 15:28.545
and...

15:30.119 --> 15:32.034
I think that's why I'm
so nervous, you know?

15:32.040 --> 15:33.515
I'm just scared I might
say the wrong thing.

15:34.781 --> 15:35.268
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:35.468 --> 15:37.186
Sometimes the most
important part of this

15:37.190 --> 15:38.437
is not what you say.

15:38.447 --> 15:40.857
It's just, uh, your
willingness to listen.

15:42.799 --> 15:43.519
[RINGING]

15:43.529 --> 15:44.392
Oh, my God. This is it.

15:45.073 --> 15:46.153
Whoa. Okay.

15:46.616 --> 15:47.238
H-Hello? Hello?

15:48.069 --> 15:48.280
Hi?

15:48.395 --> 15:49.833
I-I think it's your cellphone.

15:49.843 --> 15:51.986
[RINGING CONTINUES]

15:51.996 --> 15:53.619
I knew that. Just testing you.

15:53.629 --> 15:56.207
[RINGING STOPS]

15:57.261 --> 15:58.509
Hey. PJ.

15:58.963 --> 15:59.500
What's going on?

15:59.922 --> 16:00.752
I... just...

16:01.608 --> 16:02.711
I've been fighting with my dad again.

16:03.706 --> 16:04.009
Um...

16:05.165 --> 16:06.548
Is... Is there any
chance you can meet up?

16:08.187 --> 16:09.824
How many worms am I
allowed to bring home?

16:10.700 --> 16:11.799
None.

16:11.801 --> 16:14.135
Then can I have your
purse back for a sec?

16:15.071 --> 16:17.171
[CHUCKLES] Mom, I'm kidding.

16:17.173 --> 16:18.873
- Oh!
- [LAUGHS]

16:18.875 --> 16:20.842
No, I saw her in the parking lot.

16:20.844 --> 16:22.210
Apparently, she's back.

16:22.212 --> 16:23.911
Let's see how long this...

16:23.913 --> 16:25.213
Katherine! Hi!

16:25.215 --> 16:27.215
Eddie said you weren't
gonna be here today.

16:27.217 --> 16:29.117
- Surprise.
- [CHUCKLES]

16:29.119 --> 16:32.420
My mom had a big trial, and
it was in the Grand Canyon.

16:32.652 --> 16:34.318
Theo, give me a hand here.

16:34.320 --> 16:35.753
[GRUNTS]

16:35.755 --> 16:37.688
How's it going over here?

16:37.690 --> 16:39.724
Great... if you love worms.

16:39.726 --> 16:42.326
Theo was just telling us
about the Grand Canyon.

16:42.328 --> 16:44.362
Did you all know that the Grand Canyon

16:44.364 --> 16:46.597
slowly eroded over millions of years,

16:46.599 --> 16:48.366
- and that's how it was formed?
- Oh!

16:48.368 --> 16:50.131
Well, they don't know for sure,

16:50.134 --> 16:51.669
but that's the theory
they're going with.

16:51.671 --> 16:54.805
Either way, my mom
saved it in five days.

16:54.807 --> 16:56.941
[CHUCKLING] Well, that's very impressive.

16:56.943 --> 16:57.909
[LAUGHS]

16:57.911 --> 16:59.410
I need more soil.

17:05.617 --> 17:06.784
[THUD, RATTLING]

17:08.021 --> 17:09.520
[THUD, RATTLING]

17:11.624 --> 17:12.890
What's going on?

17:14.359 --> 17:17.127
Hard to pretend everything
is fine when it's not.

17:18.531 --> 17:19.762
I know.

17:21.800 --> 17:26.036
And being here at school just...
makes it that much harder.

17:26.038 --> 17:28.005
[PLASTIC CRINKLES]

17:28.007 --> 17:31.008
[VOICE BREAKING] I can't do this.

17:31.010 --> 17:33.110
[WHIMPERS]

17:33.112 --> 17:34.778
[SNIFFLES]

17:34.780 --> 17:37.014
Then let's not.

17:37.016 --> 17:38.815
Hey, bud, come on. We're leaving.

17:40.117 --> 17:40.739
Let's go.

17:41.082 --> 17:43.692
But we have to save
the trees and the bees.

17:43.695 --> 17:45.262
Or...

17:45.264 --> 17:47.829
we could get boba, drink
it on the car ride home.

17:49.201 --> 17:50.341
Boba.

17:50.344 --> 17:51.902
♪

17:51.904 --> 17:52.936
Come on, Mom.

17:52.938 --> 17:55.405
Let's get some boba.

17:55.407 --> 18:00.043
♪

18:00.045 --> 18:01.077
[SNIFFLES]

18:01.079 --> 18:02.345
♪

18:03.038 --> 18:04.251
What are you doing?

18:04.254 --> 18:05.739
What? This is my coat.

18:05.741 --> 18:08.306
I only tried on the other guy's
jacket. I wasn't gonna take it.

18:08.309 --> 18:11.011
I'm talking about what
you said to Delilah.

18:11.013 --> 18:12.279
I was just trying to protect her.

18:12.281 --> 18:13.160
[SCOFFS]

18:13.163 --> 18:15.939
What difference does it make
if that guy is real or not?

18:15.942 --> 18:16.954
She wants closure.

18:16.957 --> 18:18.619
I want that for her, too,
but she's not gonna get that

18:18.621 --> 18:19.920
from some hocus-pocus guy

18:19.922 --> 18:22.222
who takes advantage of people
when they're vulnerable.

18:22.500 --> 18:24.333
Hey, you guys, guess what.

18:24.335 --> 18:25.801
Elon's day's wide open.

18:25.803 --> 18:27.803
He said he could read me this afternoon.

18:27.805 --> 18:28.871
Should I do it?

18:28.873 --> 18:30.273
- Definitely.
- No.

18:30.275 --> 18:33.109
And I am going with you.

18:33.111 --> 18:34.110
- Sweet.
- Yes!

18:34.112 --> 18:35.645
I...

18:35.647 --> 18:37.880
left my keys in that dude's coat.

18:37.882 --> 18:39.148
Excuse me! Sir?

18:39.150 --> 18:40.383
- Okay. Oh! Wh... I'm sorry.
- [GIGGLING]

18:40.385 --> 18:41.984
You're over there. I
thought you were here.

18:41.986 --> 18:44.587
Oh! My bad. I thought
you were right he...

18:44.590 --> 18:46.602
Now you're over there,
though. Oh. This is...

18:46.605 --> 18:48.369
I'm terrible at this. I
don't know how to even...

18:48.374 --> 18:49.725
[ECHOING] There you go!

18:49.730 --> 18:57.967
♪

18:57.969 --> 19:04.173
♪

19:06.344 --> 19:14.684
♪

19:14.686 --> 19:20.256
♪

19:27.200 --> 19:30.013
Now, Delilah, I should tell
you that I only read people,

19:30.016 --> 19:31.282
at most, once a year.

19:31.284 --> 19:33.551
Um... how does this work?

19:33.553 --> 19:35.486
I've only seen it in movies.

19:35.488 --> 19:38.022
[CHUCKLES] I-I don't know
what movies you've seen,

19:38.024 --> 19:39.957
but, um, it's not like that.

19:39.959 --> 19:41.592
It's... [INHALES DEEPLY]

19:41.594 --> 19:44.098
It's kind of like a
daydream that I share

19:44.101 --> 19:46.464
as I communicate with the
spirit guides around you.

19:46.466 --> 19:47.832
Well, can we get to the communicating?

19:47.834 --> 19:49.767
'Cause I only have an hour in my meter.

19:52.266 --> 19:53.466
Okay.

19:53.469 --> 19:56.005
Let's... take a deep breath now.

19:56.008 --> 19:57.771
[INHALES DEEPLY]

19:57.773 --> 19:59.724
And we'll expel all the negative energy

19:59.727 --> 20:02.508
and/or people we might
have brought here today.

20:02.511 --> 20:03.610
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

20:03.612 --> 20:04.794
Okay.

20:07.528 --> 20:09.850
ANDREW: See? That's exactly
what I'm talking about.

20:09.852 --> 20:11.373
From now on, if it's
a party of six or more,

20:11.375 --> 20:12.935
we need to confirm with a credit card.

20:12.938 --> 20:15.263
We've had too many
no-shows. It's costing us money.

20:15.266 --> 20:16.289
I'm sorry.

20:16.291 --> 20:18.492
One second.

20:18.494 --> 20:20.727
Hey, Andrew, can I talk
to you for a second?

20:20.729 --> 20:22.562
Sarah, can you please excuse us?

20:26.601 --> 20:28.802
If you think we need a
new reservation policy,

20:28.804 --> 20:30.136
you need to run that by me.

20:30.138 --> 20:31.504
This is my restaurant.

20:31.506 --> 20:33.473
- Regina, I...
- I started it.

20:33.475 --> 20:34.739
[CHUCKLES]

20:34.743 --> 20:36.209
You came in at the 11th hour,

20:36.211 --> 20:38.645
and now you're putting me
on a need-to-know basis?

20:38.647 --> 20:40.180
Yeah, well, you know, honestly,

20:40.182 --> 20:41.581
when I even try to offer you

20:41.583 --> 20:43.119
the slightest bit of
constructive criticism,

20:43.121 --> 20:44.220
this is what I get.

20:45.520 --> 20:48.454
So, telling everyone how
the restaurant's gonna fail

20:48.456 --> 20:50.957
is constructive?

20:50.959 --> 20:52.925
We had an awesome brunch today.

20:52.927 --> 20:53.893
Yeah.

20:53.895 --> 20:55.895
Good brunch is great for buzz, sure.

20:55.897 --> 20:56.996
[CHUCKLES]

20:56.998 --> 20:58.598
But not for the bottom line.

20:59.000 --> 21:01.267
Regina, I've opened six
successful restaurants...

21:01.269 --> 21:03.969
Yet this is the only one
you ever seem to be at.

21:03.971 --> 21:06.238
Restaurants go up and down, Andrew.

21:06.240 --> 21:07.506
Everyone knows that.

21:07.508 --> 21:10.075
Yeah. Yeah, they do. They
go up and they go down.

21:10.077 --> 21:11.510
Then they go away.

21:11.512 --> 21:14.146
♪

21:14.148 --> 21:15.915
If you don't want to listen
to my advice, that's fine.

21:15.917 --> 21:18.350
But your psychic friend
is not the only one

21:18.352 --> 21:19.745
that can see into the future.

21:20.621 --> 21:22.321
And if you want to hear my prediction,

21:22.323 --> 21:25.090
in three months, if you don't
change things around here,

21:25.092 --> 21:26.725
this place will be gone.

21:27.862 --> 21:29.495
Mm.

21:29.497 --> 21:33.098
♪

21:34.460 --> 21:35.893
There we go, bud.

21:35.895 --> 21:36.761
[GIGGLES]

21:36.763 --> 21:37.862
Hey.

21:37.864 --> 21:39.797
Put your clothes in
the laundry room, okay?

21:39.800 --> 21:41.332
- Okay.
- Great.

21:48.107 --> 21:49.540
Katherine?

21:49.542 --> 21:54.645
♪

21:54.647 --> 21:59.784
♪

21:59.786 --> 22:01.319
Katherine?

22:01.321 --> 22:11.095
♪

22:12.365 --> 22:13.531
- Hey.
- Hey.

22:14.659 --> 22:16.025
- You okay?
- Yeah.

22:19.172 --> 22:20.571
What's...

22:20.573 --> 22:22.239
- [CHUCKLING]
- all this?

22:22.241 --> 22:24.342
When he heard you were
in the Grand Canyon,

22:24.344 --> 22:26.645
he wanted to be like you, so...

22:26.648 --> 22:27.845
we went camping.

22:27.847 --> 22:28.846
Mm.

22:30.550 --> 22:32.483
And... I didn't feel right

22:32.485 --> 22:34.151
sleeping in the bed without you.

22:39.928 --> 22:41.828
It's a mess. I know.

22:41.830 --> 22:44.598
I'll... clean it all up before I go.

22:44.600 --> 22:48.368
Maggie's letting me
stay in her old place.

22:50.872 --> 22:52.172
Wait.

22:56.211 --> 22:58.678
When I was at home,

22:58.680 --> 23:01.681
in the room I grew up in...

23:01.683 --> 23:04.443
I saw all my awards, all my ribbons...

23:04.446 --> 23:07.578
everything I worked for.

23:07.581 --> 23:10.490
Everything had its
place. It was perfect.

23:11.660 --> 23:13.827
And then I remembered a time in my life

23:13.829 --> 23:15.762
when it wasn't.

23:16.734 --> 23:19.668
A second-year law student.

23:19.670 --> 23:22.638
I was so stressed out.

23:22.640 --> 23:25.574
And I went to this random concert

23:25.576 --> 23:27.343
to blow off some steam.

23:27.345 --> 23:30.145
♪

23:30.147 --> 23:33.082
And there was this rock star on stage.

23:33.084 --> 23:35.272
He was sexy and cool.

23:35.275 --> 23:37.486
He didn't give a damn
what anyone thought of him.

23:37.488 --> 23:38.787
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

23:38.789 --> 23:41.857
My friends dared me to go
up to him after the show.

23:41.859 --> 23:44.159
He and I went for a drink.

23:44.161 --> 23:46.629
And my life was never the same.

23:46.631 --> 23:49.164
♪

23:49.166 --> 23:50.599
I spent my whole life...

23:50.601 --> 23:51.767
[INHALES SHARPLY]

23:51.769 --> 23:54.903
...planning for tomorrow.

23:54.905 --> 23:58.340
And you taught me to live for today.

23:59.889 --> 24:01.010
[CLICK]

24:01.012 --> 24:06.749
♪

24:06.751 --> 24:09.284
Well, you taught me
to believe in tomorrow.

24:09.286 --> 24:12.454
♪

24:12.456 --> 24:15.491
And I really want a tomorrow with you.

24:15.493 --> 24:17.860
♪

24:17.862 --> 24:19.928
How do we get back there?

24:19.930 --> 24:23.499
How do we become those people again?

24:23.501 --> 24:26.635
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

24:27.717 --> 24:30.818
Well, that's just it, Eddie.

24:30.820 --> 24:33.287
With this baby, we can't.

24:33.289 --> 24:35.923
[CLICK]

24:35.925 --> 24:37.692
♪

24:37.694 --> 24:39.891
And maybe...

24:39.894 --> 24:41.628
we shouldn't.

24:41.631 --> 24:44.732
♪

24:44.734 --> 24:46.801
I was thinking about
what Theo said at school,

24:46.803 --> 24:50.104
about the Grand Canyon...

24:50.106 --> 24:52.206
how the erosion, over time,

24:52.208 --> 24:55.042
gave way to something beautiful.

24:56.479 --> 25:00.248
Maybe instead of trying to
get back to what we were,

25:00.250 --> 25:02.083
we...

25:02.085 --> 25:04.318
figure out what we're gonna be.

25:04.320 --> 25:06.921
♪

25:06.923 --> 25:09.190
I'm not sure what that is right now.

25:09.192 --> 25:13.161
♪

25:14.063 --> 25:17.364
Don't go... to Maggie's.

25:19.034 --> 25:22.469
I need you to stay here and
help me get through this.

25:22.471 --> 25:25.639
♪

25:25.641 --> 25:27.841
I'll do anything for you, Katie.

25:27.843 --> 25:36.016
♪

25:36.018 --> 25:40.420
What did... she... have?

25:40.422 --> 25:43.957
♪

25:43.959 --> 25:46.293
Uh, a girl.

25:47.396 --> 25:49.166
A girl.

25:49.169 --> 25:50.335
Hmm.

25:52.434 --> 25:54.000
Congratulations.

25:54.002 --> 25:59.272
♪

25:59.274 --> 26:01.874
ELON: He's telling me that there's...

26:01.876 --> 26:04.777
there's nothing you could
have done to save him.

26:04.779 --> 26:11.150
♪

26:11.152 --> 26:13.686
And that there's a part of him...

26:13.688 --> 26:17.924
there's a part of him that's still here,

26:17.926 --> 26:20.259
that he lives on.

26:20.261 --> 26:22.981
♪

26:22.984 --> 26:24.149
He wants you to know

26:24.152 --> 26:26.299
that you were the last
thing he was thinking of

26:26.301 --> 26:28.067
before he got into that accident.

26:28.069 --> 26:30.069
♪

26:30.071 --> 26:32.605
Oh, no. It... It wasn't an accident.

26:32.607 --> 26:34.707
Um...

26:34.709 --> 26:36.200
my husband killed himself.

26:36.803 --> 26:38.636
U-Uh, no, I'm getting a car accident.

26:38.639 --> 26:39.805
Okay, we're out of here.

26:39.808 --> 26:40.779
Please be quiet.

26:40.781 --> 26:41.815
[SIGHS]

26:41.818 --> 26:43.815
He's telling me that
he's not your husband.

26:43.818 --> 26:45.384
He's...

26:45.386 --> 26:47.753
He says he's your brother.

26:47.755 --> 26:49.955
I don't have a brother.

26:49.957 --> 26:54.727
♪

26:54.729 --> 26:56.061
[VOICE BREAKING] I do.

26:56.063 --> 26:58.979
♪

27:02.099 --> 27:09.786
♪

27:09.789 --> 27:11.174
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

27:14.683 --> 27:15.802
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

27:16.919 --> 27:18.648
Where do you think he
got that coffee table?

27:18.650 --> 27:19.716
Gary, stop.

27:19.718 --> 27:22.085
I'm in the market for a coffee table.

27:22.087 --> 27:23.653
His is on my short list.

27:27.024 --> 27:30.726
Okay, I-I-I don't know
exactly how to play this.

27:30.729 --> 27:32.896
I want to be supportive.

27:32.898 --> 27:34.597
You obviously need this to be real.

27:34.599 --> 27:37.000
That is not supportive.

27:40.839 --> 27:43.373
So...

27:43.375 --> 27:45.942
you think your brother
just spoke to you?

27:49.340 --> 27:51.641
Says the guy who rubbed
his nasty-ass Bruins cap

27:51.643 --> 27:54.210
before every test
result we got this year.

27:57.205 --> 27:58.314
[SMACKS LIPS]

27:58.316 --> 27:59.482
A little music.

27:59.484 --> 28:01.083
[CLICK]

28:01.085 --> 28:03.786
♪ Do you believe in magic ♪

28:03.788 --> 28:05.488
- ♪ In a young girl... ♪
- [CLICK]

28:05.490 --> 28:07.390
[CHUCKLES]

28:07.392 --> 28:08.937
That's an unfortunate coincidence.

28:08.940 --> 28:10.059
[CLEARS THROAT]

28:10.061 --> 28:12.528
Okay, Albert, I'll be on
my cell if you need me.

28:12.530 --> 28:14.230
ALBERT: Yes, Chef.

28:14.232 --> 28:17.033
- [INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]
- ♪ I don't know where I'm headed ♪

28:17.035 --> 28:19.969
♪ Need to keep moving forward ♪

28:19.971 --> 28:22.338
♪ I don't know where I'm going ♪

28:22.340 --> 28:24.807
♪ Need to look beyond the door ♪

28:25.639 --> 28:28.106
Mm. Wow.

28:28.108 --> 28:30.542
Thank you so much for bringing this.

28:30.544 --> 28:32.364
I didn't realize how hungry I was.

28:32.367 --> 28:33.266
[CHUCKLES]

28:33.269 --> 28:34.501
You didn't have to come back.

28:34.504 --> 28:36.448
- Apparently, I did.
- Mm.

28:36.450 --> 28:37.716
Oh!

28:37.718 --> 28:40.185
Oh, here. Oh, I got that.

28:40.187 --> 28:41.993
- There.
- Thank you. You're so sweet.

28:41.996 --> 28:43.288
Yeah, maybe to you.

28:43.290 --> 28:45.924
Ohhh, I could have been...

28:45.926 --> 28:48.593
could have been a lot
nicer to Regina today.

28:50.551 --> 28:52.697
I could have handled
that conversation better.

28:55.301 --> 28:57.534
I just want what's
best for the restaurant.

28:58.471 --> 29:00.204
She knows that.

29:01.240 --> 29:02.673
How was the psychic?

29:02.675 --> 29:04.108
Oh.

29:04.110 --> 29:06.810
I didn't get what I wanted
from it. [CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

29:06.813 --> 29:08.626
You mean you still can't
think of that song, huh?

29:08.628 --> 29:09.680
[LAUGHS]

29:09.682 --> 29:11.715
It's not just that.

29:11.717 --> 29:14.184
It's... Jon.

29:14.186 --> 29:18.656
Just, I... I feel him slipping away.

29:18.658 --> 29:21.058
I'm starting to forget, and...

29:21.060 --> 29:22.726
[CHARLIE FUSSES]

29:22.728 --> 29:24.228
Shhhhh.

29:24.230 --> 29:25.829
I just don't want that to happen.

29:25.831 --> 29:29.533
I don't want to erase him.

29:29.535 --> 29:31.035
That's understandable.

29:33.345 --> 29:36.179
I haven't really been able
to look at Debra's things

29:36.182 --> 29:37.323
since she...

29:37.326 --> 29:38.842
since I lost her.

29:38.844 --> 29:41.545
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

29:41.547 --> 29:43.981
I just wish I could
talk to him, you know?

29:43.983 --> 29:45.449
Tell him how sorry I am

29:45.451 --> 29:49.753
for not seeing how much pain he was in.

29:49.755 --> 29:50.988
[CHUCKLES]

29:50.990 --> 29:52.890
This is gonna sound crazy,

29:52.892 --> 29:55.593
but there's a part of me that thinks

29:55.595 --> 29:57.661
the reason the psychic
didn't connect with him

29:57.663 --> 29:59.763
is because...

29:59.765 --> 30:02.132
Jon didn't want to talk to me.

30:03.034 --> 30:06.609
D, if it's forgiveness
you're looking for,

30:06.612 --> 30:08.645
it's not Jon that
you're gonna get it from.

30:08.648 --> 30:12.242
You... You have to forgive yourself.

30:12.244 --> 30:14.444
♪

30:14.446 --> 30:15.845
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

30:15.848 --> 30:17.962
Hey, there. How was apartment-hunting?

30:17.965 --> 30:18.996
Ohhh!

30:18.999 --> 30:21.645
I-I-I saw a cute two-bedroo...

30:21.648 --> 30:24.482
I'm not too old to
have a roommate, am I?

30:26.586 --> 30:28.152
Would you like a sandwich?

30:28.155 --> 30:29.259
[SIGHS]

30:29.261 --> 30:30.527
Thank you.

30:32.063 --> 30:33.421
Oh.

30:33.424 --> 30:35.131
Where's, uh... Where's Maggie?

30:35.133 --> 30:36.966
She's out running.

30:36.968 --> 30:38.368
Uh-oh.

30:39.360 --> 30:40.536
What'd you do?

30:40.539 --> 30:41.603
[CHUCKLES]

30:41.606 --> 30:44.530
This afternoon, we
went to see a psychic.

30:44.532 --> 30:46.732
Mm!

30:46.734 --> 30:50.509
Maggie... thinks she
made contact with Chad.

30:50.512 --> 30:51.611
Really?

30:53.807 --> 30:55.541
I'm sorry.

30:55.543 --> 30:56.975
I didn't mean to...

30:56.977 --> 30:58.844
No, no, no.

30:58.846 --> 31:00.979
After he died, I went to a psychic.

31:04.285 --> 31:05.684
I just so wanted to believe

31:05.686 --> 31:08.654
that somehow, he was still here.

31:10.624 --> 31:12.591
That's what Maggie wants.

31:12.593 --> 31:14.459
She does?

31:14.461 --> 31:15.494
[SMACKS LIPS]

31:15.496 --> 31:17.563
Yeah, I think so.

31:17.565 --> 31:19.631
♪

31:19.633 --> 31:21.133
[SIGHING] Ohh.

31:21.135 --> 31:24.002
♪

31:24.744 --> 31:26.110
[SIGHS]

31:27.447 --> 31:29.948
I still miss him so much.

31:29.950 --> 31:33.017
♪

31:33.019 --> 31:35.219
But...

31:35.221 --> 31:38.256
you cannot spend your
whole life mourning.

31:38.258 --> 31:41.871
You need to appreciate what you have

31:41.874 --> 31:43.940
instead of focusing on what you've lost.

31:44.931 --> 31:47.365
That is why I am in Boston.

31:49.302 --> 31:51.135
Does your daughter know that?

31:51.137 --> 31:53.338
♪

31:54.120 --> 31:57.054
Sometimes I don't say
anything because...

31:58.724 --> 32:01.058
...I'm afraid I'm gonna
say the wrong thing.

32:01.060 --> 32:03.822
I could learn a lesson from that.

32:03.825 --> 32:05.062
♪

32:05.064 --> 32:08.799
[SIGHS] I'm afraid that...

32:08.801 --> 32:11.869
she's not gonna feel...

32:11.871 --> 32:13.470
like I do.

32:13.472 --> 32:15.973
♪

32:15.975 --> 32:17.976
Oh, God. I am so overwhelmed.

32:17.979 --> 32:20.079
I-I mean, I don't know
what the Hell I'm doing.

32:23.206 --> 32:24.572
You know...

32:25.941 --> 32:27.207
...our friend Ed

32:27.210 --> 32:29.377
was supposed to move into
Maggie's old apartment.

32:29.379 --> 32:30.545
[SIGHS]

32:30.547 --> 32:33.398
But... he's back at his house...

32:33.401 --> 32:34.366
for now.

32:34.369 --> 32:35.917
Maybe you should ask Maggie

32:35.919 --> 32:38.553
if you can stay at her place
while you figure things out.

32:38.555 --> 32:42.189
And not because you're
too old for a roommate.

32:42.191 --> 32:43.457
[CHUCKLES]

32:43.459 --> 32:47.795
♪

32:47.797 --> 32:50.064
[GRUNTS]

32:51.074 --> 32:52.709
"Where the Red Fern Grows"?

32:54.011 --> 32:56.249
Is this how you came up
with the name of your band?

32:56.252 --> 32:57.652
Yes.

32:58.382 --> 33:01.316
My dad used to read this book
to me when I was your age.

33:01.318 --> 33:02.993
It was my favorite.

33:02.996 --> 33:04.796
You are going to love this.

33:04.799 --> 33:07.108
Now, we might cry at certain parts,

33:07.111 --> 33:09.091
but it's okay.

33:09.093 --> 33:10.926
Hey, T, brush your teeth?

33:10.928 --> 33:13.495
Hmm. He told me he did.

33:13.497 --> 33:14.850
- [LAUGHS]
- Yes.

33:14.853 --> 33:16.231
[KATHERINE CHUCKLES]

33:16.233 --> 33:18.667
Hey, Dad, now that Mom's home,

33:18.669 --> 33:20.135
are you leaving again?

33:24.274 --> 33:25.740
Well, actually, bud,

33:25.742 --> 33:29.277
Mom asked me if I could stay awhile.

33:30.019 --> 33:31.619
So, we can keep camping?

33:31.621 --> 33:33.054
Great.

33:33.056 --> 33:34.388
Mom, go grab a sleeping bag,

33:34.390 --> 33:36.691
'cause Dad's about to
read us his favorite book.

33:38.228 --> 33:41.162
Hey, Bud, I'll bet
Mom had enough camping

33:41.164 --> 33:42.997
while she was in the Grand Canyon.

33:42.999 --> 33:45.189
Why don't we let her sleep
in a real bed tonight?

33:45.192 --> 33:46.868
Alright.

33:46.870 --> 33:49.370
But if you get lonely,
we'll be right here.

33:49.372 --> 33:51.806
Thanks, T.

33:51.808 --> 33:53.140
[INHALES DEEPLY]

33:53.142 --> 33:54.308
[SMOOCHES]

33:54.310 --> 33:55.743
[GIGGLES]

33:55.745 --> 33:56.944
- Night.
- Night.

34:00.500 --> 34:02.064
[DOOR CLOSES]

34:02.068 --> 34:04.536
[CROWD CHEERING ON TV]

34:04.538 --> 34:05.638
Hey!

34:05.641 --> 34:07.805
[GRUNTS]

34:07.807 --> 34:10.208
Really sorry about earlier.

34:10.210 --> 34:11.708
I'm an ass.

34:11.710 --> 34:14.630
We've suspected it for a
while, but now we know for sure.

34:14.632 --> 34:16.880
I just spoke with your mom.

34:16.882 --> 34:18.149
[SIGHS]

34:18.150 --> 34:20.685
She told me how much she misses Chad.

34:20.687 --> 34:22.120
Yeah, of course she did.

34:22.121 --> 34:26.257
No, Mags, she said she needs
to realize what she still has.

34:26.259 --> 34:28.493
She means you.

34:28.495 --> 34:31.059
♪

34:31.063 --> 34:33.998
I-I don't know if Chad was trying to...

34:34.000 --> 34:35.396
connect with you today.

34:35.399 --> 34:36.634
I hope he was.

34:36.636 --> 34:40.103
But I do know who is trying
to, and that's your mother.

34:40.106 --> 34:41.904
And that's why she's in Boston.

34:41.907 --> 34:44.375
♪

34:44.377 --> 34:48.060
Now, she asked me for a
restaurant recommendation,

34:48.063 --> 34:50.748
and I didn't say Gina's,
because, you know...

34:50.750 --> 34:52.607
[WHISPERING] boundaries.

34:52.610 --> 34:54.319
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

34:54.321 --> 34:56.646
[NORMAL VOICE] But I may
have texted her a place.

34:56.649 --> 34:58.289
[SIGHS]

34:58.291 --> 35:00.419
So, she's just sitting by herself

35:00.422 --> 35:01.957
at a restaurant right now?

35:01.960 --> 35:04.494
She said she wanted to get
out of your hair for a while...

35:04.497 --> 35:06.764
which... I know, I know... is
not the coolest thing to say

35:06.766 --> 35:08.833
about your daughter who
just went through chemo.

35:08.835 --> 35:10.568
[SCOFFS] Exactly.

35:11.571 --> 35:13.738
She doesn't want to connect with me.

35:13.740 --> 35:16.374
Then why is she here?

35:16.376 --> 35:24.215
♪

35:24.217 --> 35:27.585
Take it from a guy whose mom
never flew anywhere to see him.

35:27.587 --> 35:30.477
♪

35:30.480 --> 35:33.658
Your mom is sitting by
herself in a restaurant.

35:33.660 --> 35:35.026
So go.

35:35.028 --> 35:38.029
♪

35:38.031 --> 35:39.697
Talk to her.

35:39.699 --> 35:42.360
♪

35:42.363 --> 35:43.963
[SIGHS]

35:47.811 --> 35:52.122
[MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

35:52.133 --> 35:53.466
Excuse me.

35:53.468 --> 35:55.468
Is there a woman here dining alone

35:55.470 --> 35:57.870
who's basically me in her 50s?

35:57.872 --> 35:59.005
On the outside.

35:59.007 --> 36:01.207
On the inside, we're
very, very different.

36:01.209 --> 36:04.410
No. And your whole party must
be present before I can seat you.

36:04.412 --> 36:06.546
Oh, okay. I'll just wait for her, then.

36:06.548 --> 36:07.880
Well, you can wait at the bar.

36:07.882 --> 36:10.249
This area is for people
who are ready to be seated.

36:11.953 --> 36:13.619
The bar it is.

36:13.621 --> 36:15.588
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

36:15.590 --> 36:21.728
♪

36:21.730 --> 36:23.496
[SIGHS]

36:23.498 --> 36:25.698
♪

36:26.500 --> 36:27.766
Welcome to the support group

36:27.768 --> 36:29.736
for people who have
been abused by that guy.

36:29.739 --> 36:32.403
May I recommend the Chardonnay?

36:32.406 --> 36:35.073
Oh, Chardonnay is for
passive-aggressive.

36:35.075 --> 36:37.721
For aggressive-aggressive, I need vodka.

36:39.229 --> 36:41.140
Well, don't take it personally.

36:41.143 --> 36:42.702
He's picking on 10-year-olds now.

36:42.705 --> 36:43.916
I don't know where those hands have been.

36:43.918 --> 36:45.017
There's a spoon here for a reason.

36:45.019 --> 36:46.118
Dude, chill!

36:46.120 --> 36:47.166
Oh.

36:47.369 --> 36:49.721
In his defense, I'm pretty
sure the kid started it.

36:49.723 --> 36:51.523
[LAUGHS]

36:51.525 --> 36:52.557
[CHUCKLES]

36:52.559 --> 36:54.659
The vodka's on me if you go over there

36:54.661 --> 36:57.295
and grab a handful of mints
without using the spoon.

36:57.297 --> 36:59.164
♪

36:59.166 --> 37:00.699
Do I have to eat them?

37:00.701 --> 37:01.767
Oh, God, no.

37:01.769 --> 37:03.468
It's like a peppermint septic tank.

37:03.470 --> 37:05.270
[LAUGHS]

37:06.206 --> 37:08.140
Come ooooooon.

37:08.142 --> 37:10.809
[SIGHS] God, he just doesn't get me.

37:10.811 --> 37:12.044
He never will.

37:12.046 --> 37:13.378
[SCOFFS]

37:13.380 --> 37:15.781
I'm... I'm just not the
son that he wanted me to be.

37:17.020 --> 37:19.120
Must be really frustrating.

37:19.122 --> 37:21.555
I feel the same way about
my old man sometimes.

37:21.557 --> 37:23.124
- You do?
- Yeah.

37:23.126 --> 37:24.759
Then he'll say something
or do something,

37:24.761 --> 37:26.560
and I realize we're
more alike than I think,

37:26.562 --> 37:28.329
[CHUCKLING] which pisses me off even more.

37:28.331 --> 37:29.697
[CHUCKLES]

37:31.334 --> 37:32.633
This thing work?

37:32.635 --> 37:33.801
Yeah.

37:33.803 --> 37:36.134
I actually shot my
thesis on it in college.

37:36.137 --> 37:37.505
You went to film school?

37:37.507 --> 37:39.740
Little less judgment, bruh.

37:39.742 --> 37:41.580
You're starting to sound like my dad.

37:41.583 --> 37:42.743
[CHUCKLES]

37:42.745 --> 37:44.009
Yeah, try telling a firefighter

37:44.013 --> 37:45.446
that you want to go to art school.

37:45.448 --> 37:47.114
[LAUGHS]

37:48.117 --> 37:53.621
♪

37:53.813 --> 37:55.212
Who's this guy?

37:55.214 --> 37:57.114
That's my boy Gary.

37:57.116 --> 37:58.682
No, no, not him.

37:58.684 --> 38:00.518
Him.

38:00.520 --> 38:02.620
Oh.

38:02.622 --> 38:03.821
That's Jon.

38:03.823 --> 38:05.456
He, uh...

38:05.458 --> 38:08.025
He died last year.

38:08.027 --> 38:09.693
He killed himself.

38:12.131 --> 38:13.330
He was so fun.

38:13.332 --> 38:14.932
[CHUCKLING] You'd have loved him.

38:14.934 --> 38:17.535
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

38:17.537 --> 38:20.204
[DOOR OPENS]

38:20.206 --> 38:21.705
- Hey, babe.
- [DOOR CLOSES]

38:21.707 --> 38:22.940
Hey, Gina.

38:22.942 --> 38:24.758
I want you to meet my friend PJ.

38:24.761 --> 38:26.877
♪

38:26.879 --> 38:28.245
[CHARLIE COOS]

38:28.247 --> 38:30.381
DELILAH: I am so sorry, sweetie.

38:30.383 --> 38:33.918
I can't remember the name of that song.

38:34.820 --> 38:38.655
Jon could sing it better
than I could, anyway.

38:38.657 --> 38:43.259
And I know that it's complicated
how you came into this world.

38:45.197 --> 38:46.763
[SIGHS]

38:46.765 --> 38:48.631
But you're not alone.

38:48.633 --> 38:52.035
And I love you so very much.

38:52.037 --> 38:54.871
And while I'm at it,

38:54.873 --> 38:57.340
[SIGHS] I may as well
go ahead and apologize

38:57.342 --> 39:00.610
for every mistake I'm
gonna make in your life.

39:00.612 --> 39:02.445
There'll probably be a ton of them.

39:02.447 --> 39:05.181
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

39:05.183 --> 39:10.086
The reason I'm doing this
now is because sometimes...

39:10.088 --> 39:13.089
you don't get a chance to say it later.

39:13.091 --> 39:16.893
♪

39:17.320 --> 39:19.720
So I just wanted to get ahead of it

39:19.722 --> 39:24.358
and tell you that I'm sorry
for all the things I've done.

39:25.561 --> 39:26.994
Oh, my God.

39:26.996 --> 39:29.330
[GASPS] That's it.

39:29.332 --> 39:30.965
That's the song.

39:32.335 --> 39:36.237
♪ How many times do I have to tell you ♪

39:36.239 --> 39:40.880
♪ That I'm sorry for
the things I've done? ♪

39:40.883 --> 39:44.712
♪ Why-y-y-y-y-y? ♪

39:44.714 --> 39:48.082
Hey, Andrew. It's Regina.

39:48.084 --> 39:50.117
I was thinking about
what you said earlier,

39:50.119 --> 39:53.688
and I want you to know that...

39:53.690 --> 39:55.690
I heard you.

39:55.692 --> 39:58.993
Call me when you can so we
can talk about your ideas.

39:59.002 --> 40:00.301
Thanks.

40:02.798 --> 40:08.335
♪ How many times do I
have to try to tell you ♪

40:08.337 --> 40:10.737
"It's strange indeed how
memories can lie dormant

40:10.739 --> 40:13.240
in a man's mind for so many years."

40:14.079 --> 40:16.254
Theo, you can't go
camping in the Grand Canyon

40:16.257 --> 40:17.723
without a canteen.

40:19.048 --> 40:20.547
- Move over.
- Oh.

40:20.549 --> 40:22.015
Just in time, Mom.

40:22.017 --> 40:23.717
We're about to get to the good part.

40:23.719 --> 40:25.052
[CHUCKLES]

40:25.054 --> 40:26.954
♪ That's when you have to tell me ♪

40:26.956 --> 40:29.323
"Yet those memories can be awakened

40:29.325 --> 40:31.425
and brought forth fresh and new,

40:31.427 --> 40:35.629
just by something you've seen
or something you've heard,

40:35.631 --> 40:38.532
or the sight of an old, familiar face."

40:40.035 --> 40:43.971
It's okay, Mom. Dad said
we may cry at some parts.

40:43.973 --> 40:47.641
♪ That's why it hurts so
bad to hear the words ♪

40:47.643 --> 40:50.739
♪ That keep on falling from your mouth ♪

40:50.745 --> 40:51.811
Excuse me.

